    <stitle>HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION WITH TRAILING LEAF SPRINGS - HENDRICKSON AIR SUSPENSION COMPONENTS - SHOCK
        ABSORBERS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SHOCK ABSORBERS</title>
        <para>Each axle is controlled by a hydraulic shock absorber mounted by the air spring (bag) where shock travel
            is greatest to provide maximum control (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0300708">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
        </para>
        <figure id="f0300708" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0300708" filename="../figg03/g0300708.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 8. AIR SPRING AND SHOCK ABSORBER ASSEMBLY</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1.AIR SPRING (BAG) FRAME HANGER</callout1>
                <callout1>2.SHOCK ABSORBER FRAME HANGER</callout1>
                <callout1>3.LOCKNUT/WASHER</callout1>
                <callout1>4.SHOCK ABSORBER</callout1>
                <callout1>5.AIR SPRING (BAG)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
